The schedule includes a new Rugby Championship venue, with Trafalgar Park in Nelson to host the New Zealand v Argentina Test on September 8. The venue for the Springboks’ match against Argentina was also confirmed as Estadio Malvinas Argentinas in Mendoza on August 25. The venues for the Springboks’ other matches were confirmed at an earlier date. The Rugby Championship kicks-off on August 18 when the Wallabies take on reigning champions the All Blacks in Sydney and concludes on October 6 when Argentina host Australia in Salta. --News24--